JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 2
SP  - 293
EP  - 300
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - An important question is how well competitive models approximate models of large finite economies. For a class of differentiated products models static Nash equilibria, if they exist, always converge to competition as the number of firms increases. Dynamic Nash equilibria need not so converge. Easily checked conditions for convergence to competition do, however, exist.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297518
